fvar instance name 'Light' is different to constructed STAT table name '144pt Light S100'. This may cause issues in applications.
This might be related to wrong ordering of axis in the STAT table, or wrong/different names or different use of abbreviations. Please double check names of STAT and fvar table.

STAT

axis ordering

Check STAT table axis ordering.

STAT table axis 'wght' has order number '1', but should be '3'.
This has an impact how it is sorted in drop down menus, for example in Adobe InDesign or MS Word. Please ignore this if the sorting is intended.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Fraunces Black' ≠ 'Fraunces 144pt S100 Black' (NID 1).
